import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='year', y='fertility', label='Fertility Rate')
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='year', y='life_expect', label='Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility rate and life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='fertility', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("Which countries have the highest and lowest fertility rates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
